FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: The Newbie</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">You will note that my post specifically stated &quot;newbie beggars&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Attrition&quot; applies, in general, to a workplace environment.  This is because the demand to work at one place is, in general, equivalent to the demand to work in another.  Games are different, because there are not a fixed number of accounts in the way that there are a fixed number of positions to be filled at a company.  Unlike &quot;better&quot; companies, there will always be &quot;openings&quot; in &quot;better&quot; games for the influx of new people.  However, games are unlike companies also in the fact that it is quite possible to play multiple games, whereas it is next to impossible to work fulltime at more than one (or perhaps 2) jobs.  <br>
<br>
I think you would be hard-pressed to find any high level who deems it necessary to spend the majority of his or her time going around making newbie lives miserable.  The newbies claiming that higher level players are jerks generally base those claims upon situations in which they were begging or in some other way acting inappropriately to the high level player to deserve it.  Personally I prefer to avoid newbie zones whenever possible due to the influx of requests for buffs, ports, sows, and items I get whenever I get near one, along with the unpleasantness that results when I refuse.  I have much better things to do with my time than taunt newbies.  Those newbies who choose to make my life miserable by being demanding are, in my opinion, fair game when it comes to telling them off, and if my telling them off causes them to leave the game then, quite frankly, I'm glad.  The game is better off without low level whining beggars who believe the world revolves around them.  I will, and have repeatedly, gone out of my way to help out true newbies who are polite and grateful.  I love helping newbies who are polite and grateful.  I hate even being near newbies who are nasty little beggar scum.<br>
<br>
And again, I'm curious.  Why do some people seem to be under the impression that EQ will last forever if we do something to make it?  Why do some people want EQ to last forever?  I'm sure there will be better (or at least different and equivalent) games for me to waste my time playing in the future.<br>
<br>
-fel<br>
